<%- include("partials/header") %>

<div class="container-fluid bg-light" style="min-height: calc(100vh - 70px);">
  <div class="row h-100">

    <!-- Sidebar -->
    <div class="col-lg-3 col-xl-2 border-end bg-white p-0 d-none d-lg-block">
      <div class="p-4 border-bottom">
        <h6 class="text-uppercase fw-bold text-muted mb-0" style="font-size: 0.75rem; letter-spacing: 1px;">
          Your Library
        </h6>
      </div>

      <div class="list-group list-group-flush">
        <a href="#"
          class="list-group-item list-group-item-action bg-primary bg-opacity-10 border-start border-4 border-primary py-3">
          <div class="d-flex w-100 justify-content-between align-items-center mb-1">
            <h6 class="mb-0 fw-bold text-dark text-truncate">Q3 Product Roadmap...</h6>
            <span class="badge bg-danger rounded-pill" style="font-size: 0.6rem;">LIVE</span>
          </div>
          <small class="text-muted">Today, 10:30 AM</small>
        </a>
      </div>
    </div>

    <!-- Main Content -->
    <div class="col-lg-9 col-xl-10 p-4 p-lg-5">

      <!-- Header -->
      <div class="d-flex flex-column flex-md-row justify-content-between align-items-md-center mb-4 gap-3">
        <div>
          <span class="badge bg-danger bg-opacity-10 text-danger rounded-pill px-3 py-1 mb-2 fw-semibold border border-danger border-opacity-25">
            <i class="bi bi-record-circle me-1"></i> Live Meeting Source
          </span>
          <h2 class="fw-bold text-dark mb-1">Q3 Product Roadmap Planning</h2>
          <p class="text-muted mb-0">
            <i class="bi bi-calendar3 me-2"></i>
            April 19, 2026 • 5m 0s duration • 72 Participants
          </p>
        </div>
      </div>

      <!-- Tabs -->
      <ul class="nav nav-tabs mb-4 border-bottom" id="meetingTabs" role="tablist">
        <li class="nav-item">
          <button class="nav-link active fw-bold px-4 py-3 text-dark"
            data-bs-toggle="tab" data-bs-target="#summary">
            Overview & Insights
          </button>
        </li>
        <li class="nav-item">
          <button class="nav-link fw-bold px-4 py-3 text-muted"
            data-bs-toggle="tab" data-bs-target="#transcript">
            Full Transcript
          </button>
        </li>
      </ul>

      <div class="tab-content">

        <!-- SUMMARY TAB -->
        <div class="tab-pane fade show active" id="summary">
          <div class="row g-4">

            <div class="col-xl-8">
              <div class="bg-white border rounded-4 p-4 shadow-sm mb-4">
                <h5 class="fw-bold mb-3">
                  <i class="bi bi-card-text text-primary"></i>
                  Executive Summary
                </h5>
                <p class="text-muted">
                  <%= notes?.summary || "Processing..." %>
                </p>
              </div>

              <div class="bg-white border rounded-4 p-4 shadow-sm">
                <h5 class="fw-bold mb-3">
                  <i class="bi bi-lightbulb text-warning"></i>
                  Key Concepts
                </h5>

                <ul class="list-group list-group-flush">
                  <% notes?.key_concepts?.forEach(concept => { %>
                    <li class="list-group-item px-0">
                      <i class="bi bi-check-circle text-primary me-2"></i>
                      <%= concept %>
                    </li>
                  <% }) %>
                </ul>
              </div>
            </div>

            <div class="col-xl-4">
              <!-- Optional sidebar -->
            </div>

          </div>
        </div>

        <!-- TRANSCRIPT TAB -->
        <div class="tab-pane fade" id="transcript">
          <div class="bg-white border rounded-4 shadow-sm p-4" style="max-height: 500px; overflow-y: auto;">

            <div class="d-flex gap-3 mb-4">
              <div class="bg-primary text-white rounded-circle d-flex align-items-center justify-content-center fw-bold"
                style="width: 45px; height: 45px;">S</div>
              <div>
                <div class="d-flex gap-2 mb-1">
                  <h6 class="fw-bold mb-0">Speaker</h6>
                  <span class="text-muted small">10:00 AM</span>
                </div>
                <p class="text-muted mb-0">
                  Very simple, right? Now, before I move ahead, I just want to see, I see a lot of people in the, let me stop the sharing. Wow, we have what 72 participants. Let's run a poll and see who's here. So what I'm going to do is I'm going to run a poll now and share the results with you. So first poll I have is, what's your experience using Zoom? Rate yourself. Are you an expert? This is your first time. I'm going to do a poll. Please accept my apologies that I won't be able to monitor the chat because I found to do I'm not that much of a multitasking guy. So I will look at the chat maybe later on and then maybe host responses in the. What's up group? So we have a good amount of responses. And I will end the polling in three to one. So as you can see, we have some flash timers. Some who have attended Zoom meetings. Some have conducted meetings and we have two experts, which is great. Right, we can share from each other and understand. Okay, I'll do one more poll. Because I want to know where I hold from. I'm going to do a poll. Yeah, it is willing. I'm happy to see so many of members of my. Those masters from bar and joining us. Excellent. I will close the poll in three to one. So as we can see, we have people who have attended this meeting for the first time. So for them, it might be little overwhelming to go to the Zoom and create a meeting from scratch. That's why I have created the WhatsApp group. I want you all if you are really interested in doing your own Zoom meetings. As I said, go to zoom.com, create an account. Follow the instruction that I have shared and I'll be sharing the PowerPoint also in the WhatsApp group. Create the meeting. Maybe in the initial stage, just have a meeting with two or three people. Then you can practice for your actual dose master meeting. Make a trial run with your XCOM maybe. See how it works. And then you can do the actual dose master meeting. Now we move into the controls related to. Like how did I create this poll? How did I share the poll with you all? And how could you do? So you could use a poll like this, for example, in a dose master meeting for choosing the best speaker. Or the best table topic, best role player. So now you have one role less required in dose master meetings. You don't need a vote counter. Correct? Because the dose master of the day will create the polls. And once the speaking segment is over, launch the poll. And that's it. You know, you know, you're who's the best speaker. And we will do that for the table topics by the way today. Now comes. Once the meeting started. So basically that I have started created this meeting. Whenever you are ready to start.
                </p>
              </div>
            </div>

          </div>
        </div>

      </div>

    </div> <!-- END Main Content -->

  </div> <!-- END Row -->
</div> <!-- END Container -->

<%- include("partials/footer") %>